  "summary": "preinstall script exfiltrates /flag.txt to hardcoded remote IP",
  "details": "On npm install, the package.json preinstall lifecycle hook reads /flag.txt from the installer's filesystem and either copies it to a publicly served static directory (/app/public/static/flag.txt or /app/static/flag.txt) or POSTs its contents over plain HTTP to a hardcoded remote endpoint at 10.107.121.85:8000/flag. The package has no legitimate functionality and exists solely to read installer-side filesystem content and send it off-host to an attacker-controlled IP. This fires automatically on default install with no user interaction.",
